Given this code:

const form = this.fb.group({
  tags: this.fb.array([])
});
const tagsArray = form.get('tags') as FormArray;
tagsArray.push(this.fb.control('angular'));
tagsArray.push(this.fb.control('rxjs'));
tagsArray.removeAt(0);

What is the value of tagsArray.value after all operations?

Given this routing configuration:
{ path: '**', redirectTo: '/not-found' }

Where should this wildcard route be placed in the routes array?

Given this interceptor:

export const loggingInterceptor: HttpInterceptorFn = (req, next) => {
  console.log('Request:', req.url);
  return next(req).pipe(
    tap(event => {
      if (event instanceof HttpResponse) {
        console.log('Response:', event.status);
      }
    })
  );
};

What does this interceptor do?

Given this RxJS code:

const a$ = interval(1000).pipe(take(3));
const b$ = interval(500).pipe(take(3));
combineLatest([a$, b$]).subscribe(console.log);

When does combineLatest first emit?

Given this signal-based code:

const count = signal(0);
const doubled = computed(() => count() * 2);
count.set(5);
console.log(doubled());

What does doubled() return?

Given this pipe usage in a template:

{{ largeList | filterByName:searchTerm }}

If filterByName is a pure pipe, when will it re-execute?

Given this test:

const mockService = jasmine.createSpyObj('DataService', ['getData']);
mockService.getData.and.returnValue(of([{ id: 1 }]));

What does mockService.getData() return when called?

Given this code:

const clicks$ = fromEvent(document, 'click');
const result$ = clicks$.pipe(
  debounceTime(300),
  distinctUntilChanged()
);

What does distinctUntilChanged() do in this context?
